quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  34,46,"Say: I admonish you in but one thing: That you stand up for God by twos and one by one. Again, reflect. There is not in your companion any madness. He is only a warner to you of a severe punishment in advance of you"
  34,47,"Say: Whatever compensation I asked of you, that is for you. My compensation is only from God. And He is a Witness over everything"
  34,48,"Say: Truly, my Lord hurls The Truth. He is The Knower of the unseen"
  34,49,"Say: The Truth drew near and falsehood neither causes to begin nor causes to return"
  34,50,"Say: If I went astray, truly, I will only go astray with loss for myself. And if I was truly guided, it is because of what my Lord reveals to me. Truly, He is Hearing, Ever Near"
  34,51,"And if thou wouldst see when they would be terrified, when there is no escape and they would be taken from a near place"
  34,52,"they would say: We believed in it! But how could they reach it from a place so far away"
  34,53,"And, surely, they were ungrateful for it before. And they hurl at the unseen from a far place"
  34,54,"And a barrier was set up between them and between that for which they lust just as was accomplished with partisans before. Truly, they had been uncertain, in grave doubt"